The paper proposes a deep network architecture for image denoising, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep learning and neural networks suggests that it could also belong to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of GPU computing, which suggests it could belong to multimedia (cs.MM) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories.
